<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Abeille (1877: 6) wrote that the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysis splendidula" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidula">Chrysis splendidula</taxonomicName>
is housed in the Spinola collection. This was likely erroneous information, since the syntypes are expected to be housed in MNHU, together with other 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rossi’s">Rossi's</normalizedToken>
types. And we also found no evidence for the type in the Spinola collection.
</paragraph>
